This form of illustration originated from my childhood, when my cousin wanted to teach me drawing with the help of geometric shapes.
 The clothes that the mullah wears cause his body to take on abstract forms. I did not know exactly what was under that dress!
In the hidden layers that can not be expressed, I try to express my point of view about their actions with the movements I give them.
